name: phylo.js
tagline: Javascript library for phylogenetic tree manipulation and visualisation.
body:
This is a short JavaScript library for parsing [Newick](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newick_format) representations of phylogenetic trees and visualizing the results using [SVG](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SVG).

* Example web app: [DendrOgle](viewer.html)
note: Don't delete this file! It's used internally to help with page regeneration.
